HUNDREDS of Outlander fans from all over the world descended on Scotland this weekend to visit sites featured in the hit series.The 200-strong Outlandish Gathering 2015, included visits to Doune Castle in Perthshire, which has seen a 30% increase in visitor numbers.Scenes from the time-travel drama starring Sam Heughan and Caitriona Balfe were also filmed in Glasgow and Rannoch Moor.A second series has now gone into production in Cumbernauld.VisitScotland is now planning to launch a major Outlander push in Germany.